The White House Press Secretary has released a statement expressing support for the Senate's introduction of the Home Star Energy Retrofit Act. This legislation aims to provide incentives for homeowners to make their homes more energy-efficient. The statement highlights the potential benefits of the bill, including job creation, cost savings for consumers, and economic strengthening. The program is designed to help middle-class homeowners invest in energy-efficient products such as windows, water heaters, and air conditioners. The White House is looking forward to collaborating with the Senate to ensure a smooth implementation of the program.